properties.value: An unfinished crunchy is an item created in gnome cooking by cooking a half made crunchy on a range. The unfinished crunchy can be garnished with gnome spice, chocolate dust or equa leaves, as specified in the recipe, to create the finished toad crunchies, spicy crunchies, worm crunchies or chocchip crunchies.

content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:Unfinished crunchy

An unfinished crunchy is an item created in gnome cooking by cooking a half made crunchy on a range. The unfinished crunchy can be garnished with gnome spice, chocolate dust or equa leaves, as specified in the recipe, to create the finished toad crunchies, spicy crunchies, worm crunchies or chocchip crunchies.

  • Unfinished crunchy (worm)

An '''unfinished crunchy''' is an item created in [[gnome cooking]] by cooking a [[half made crunchy]] on a [[range]]. The unfinished crunchy can be garnished with [[gnome spice]], [[chocolate dust]] or [[equa leaves]], as specified in the recipe, to create the finished [[toad crunchies]], [[spicy crunchies]], [[worm crunchies]] or [[chocchip crunchies]].
